data.name: richTextBox12.Text
data.value:
LSKs or Line Select Keys (highlighted in the picture below) surround the display allowing selection of modes or copying/pasting of information.
The LSKs are labeled (starting at the top left button, working down) L1-L6 and (for the right side buttons) R1-R6.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
Pressing the R1 button from the Mission Power page will toggle power for the V/U1 radio.
Pressing the R2 button from the Mission Power page will toggle power for the V/U2 radio.
Selecting RETURN will display the START INIT page.

data.name: richTextBox10.Text
data.value: Pressing the L4 button will display the COM STATUS page. This page displays the status of all Mission Communication systems that are tied into the 1553 data bus chain. In this example, VU1 and VU2 indicate a fault while the HF system indicates a GO status.

data.name: richTextBox9.Text
data.value: Notice the yellow NGO indication under the COM title. NGO indicates a NO-GO condition. In this example, a failure of a communication system is generating a NGO condition. Because this is the first visit to this page, the NGO text is highlighted yellow. Any subsequent visits to this page will show white text unless the condition changes.

data.name: richTextBox16.Text
data.value: Each radio is functioning normally unless an exclamation point precedes the radio title, like “!V/U1” in the figure below. In these cases, access the STATUS page for the specific radio for more information.

data.name: richTextBox17.Text
data.value:
Recalling Presets: 1. Last Frequency Recall: A scratchpad entry of "0" followed by L1 press. 2. Call Sign Recall: A scratchpad entry of a valid call sign followed by L1 press. 3. Preset Number Recall: A scratchpad entry of a valid preset number followed by L1 press.
Changing presets: 1. COMSEC Mode/Net Change: A scratchpad entry of a valid COMSEC mode/net followed by R1 press. 2. Frequency Change: A scratchpad entry of a valid frequency followed by R1 press.
VU2 and HF work in the same manner.
